replies.text:
@timothyvanhoeck233 
*"Disney Wars ain't canon.  Doesn't matter how much they claim otherwise."*
That's not really how canon works, though. I hate Disney Wars as much as anyone, but that doesn't actually change reality. If you want to ignore it, by all means, feel free to do so. I certainly do. I've been running the old West End Games Star Wars RPG since the early '90s, before the prequels came out, and I've ignored plenty of things Lucas put into the PT, too.

@maxmazzotti6651 True.. but tell me really, has 343 industries done any favors to Halo to make it somewhat relevant these past like.. 5 years? I can't think of much. Mostly bad honestly. And a lot of lies. Also what tv show you thinking of? Halo tv show or Last of Us tv show, both.. well, one was a disaster off the start, the other get the nostalgia bait, then did the second game's plotline, and crashed and burned. 

Halo is definitely a cultural staple of gaming and we'll always love the good we had. Just it's a seriously degraded franchise as well.

The halo tv show just reminded us that 343 industries/Microsoft (or halo studios, lol) is an absolute directionless, unorganized mess.

@maxmazzotti6651 

I agreed with you. Halo is a standing Icon that is infinitely more impactful on gaming as a whole then Last of Us. Just Last of us IP crashed and burned so fast in the presence of gaming in  general  that it's probably more well known on it's failures.

Also don't care if Halo tv show is canon or not, it was absolutely shit show, disservice to all characters. Deserves all the criticism it gets.

@michaelwills1926Just the other day some actor was recalling a story about his run-ins with Jack Nicholson over the years. You'd think he was talking about a living God - tearing up at the memory of receiving a compliment. "That meant the world to me, coming from someone that truly mattered"
... What freaking universe do these weirdos live in? Adult pretenders literally crying at the thought of getting compliments from other adult pretenders. 
What a shame that the writers and *actual* talent have to see their divinely inspired creations trampled so disrespectfully by this industry of deranged self-infatuated children who never grew up.

