It was clearly an effort to sell teddy bears, rather than a good story idea.  Everyone knew it.  It's how you get to the "Chewbacca Defense."  The beginning of the end.

@AbstractM0use 
*"You think we don't inherit cells and mitochondria from our parents?"*
FFS, you biologically illiterate clown. Mitocondria _are organelles contained in nearly all cells._ While there are cells without mitochondria, there are NEVER mitochondria floating around without being contained within cells. And you don't INHERIT cells from your parents, genius. You inherit GENES. Once the sperm and egg are combined, 100% of the cells that grow within the newly created organism are exclusive to *THAT ORGANISM.*

